rComments: He is not clear in his lectures, sometime he is too fast and sometimes he is too slow. Some days he is grumpy and wants to end the class asap. You need to follow up on the emails to get an answer. The slides are incomplete, he leaves much to study for yourself. The final exam was too hard and the assignments are unnecessarily complicated.

The lectures are boring, exams are unnecessarily hard and the grading is way too tough imo. Wouldn't recommend at all and wouldn't take again. It's a tough class so if the teacher doesn't help much, it's awful.
Professor Ozturk is a good teacher who is always present for his students. He knows that the subject is very complicated but he is there if you need help. Work hard and everything will be fine.

He explains tough materials in an easy-to-understand way and truly cares about his students' understanding. Even though I'm in French Immersion, I have no issue understanding his French and still managed to do well in the course. Highly recommend!

Professor Ozturk is very knowledgeable and explains the material very well. If anything is unclear, he's willing to explain after class or during office hours. The quizzes, midterm and final are very fair, just make sure to go to class and study and everything be go just fine.

Ses exams et quiz sont absolument aléatoires. On peut avoir un exercice super simple ou encore très complexe car il a besoin de baisser ses moyennes. Cela donne des résultats peu représentatifs de la compréhension.

Mr. Ozturk is a caring prof. He makes sure that he is teaching something to his student. As much as his class has a heavy material, he takes his time if the student is willing to learn during office h. He is bilingual which is pretty cool. You should be continuously repeating what you learn to pass with a good grade, that class is actually fun!

Onur Ozturk is a nightmare of a teacher. He comes off as knowledgeable on his field but completely lacks what it takes to be a good teacher. He teaches in a very monotone boring way and expects you to basically know the difficult subject already. His quizzes are hard and he only gives 30 minutes to complete them. STAY AWAY AT ALL COSTS!

He communicates properly and makes sure that the students learned the topic in class. He is smart and knowledgable. I really liked that he can speak English and French. I had some questions and visited him in his office. He is patient and explained my questions properly in French. The course was not easy but he makes it easier. Recommended.

He's a knowledgeable guy, but expects lots of student participation. He'll call on people for answers and wait for people to ask questions. Grading material is straight forward and very similar to practice work. Definitely recommend if you have to take a hard class like this one.

Onur is a really caring prof, he truly wants his students to pass. The course itself is really hard of its own. He is ready to help outside his class. Midterm was not easy but it seemed okay after he explained it. The final was easier compared to quizzes and the midterm. Most of the questions of the final was pretty similar to the examples.
He is a really good prof, he knows what he is doing and he has knowledge, he is also really helpful, and really wants his students to have a good grade. i would definetly take his class again

Not easy class at all. The prof doesn't explain well that make it very difficult. DGD recommended to try to understand a bit, be ready to practice a lot at home! 2 homework to do in a group, pretty hard. 2 tough quiz in class in 20 mins, he always says everything it's easy. He gave extra points if you go to see him because the marks are pretty low.

Professor Onur is very knowledgeable in his field and has studied it for years. This leads him to over estimate the capabilities of his students, giving overcomplicated exam questions and unrealistic time limits. He has a difficult time conveying the information and generally can't explain the concepts in various ways when students are confused.

He's a teacher that knows what he's talking about, but he explains as if we already know the chapters. He cares about his students, but he's tricky he puts very hard stuff in exams. he used questions from passed quiz for the last quiz instead of the new chapters. He seems to be as tired and not motivated as we were in his class.

In my opinion, Onur is a good teacher. He explains every concept with examples. The exams/quiz are composed entirely of those examples (with different numbers). 2 warnings for his class : 1. He sighs a lot (maybe 10-20 times per class... can be discouraging). 2. He doesn't give enough time to complete the quizzes (barely have time to read them)
